    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nSince upgrading to 0.12 I've noticed a buggy behavior related to lsp completions.  It seems to reliably trigger when completing via an autotrigger character? (I'm not certain that is the correct terminology).  The inserted text is highlighted sort of like visual mode but if you press escape it remains highlighted forever until you manually dirty the characters.\n\nasciinema recording: https://asciinema.org/a/948576\n\n<hr>\n\nAs a side note, how can I disable this autocompletion?  It is not very helpful since what it inserts is poorly formatted and syntactially invalid.  I'd prefer all completions to have to go through the regular completion menu. I tried adding the below snippet and it didn't seem to have any effect?\n\n```\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('LspAttach', {\n  callback = function(args)\n    local client = vim.lsp.get_client_by_id(args.data.client_id)\n\n    if client:supports_method('textDocument/completion') then\n      vim.lsp.completion.enable(true, client.id, args.buf, {\n        autotrigger = false,\n      })\n    end\n  end\n})\n```\n\n### Steps to reproduce using \"nvim --clean -u minimal_init.lua\"\n\nTo reproduce: \n1. `nvim --clean -u minimal.lua test.c`\n2. Position your cursor just after a bare function name\n3. Invoke omnicomplete <C-x> <C-o>\n4. Type (\n5. Type Esc\n\n`minimal.lua`\n```\nvim.lsp.config('clangd', {\n  cmd = { 'clangd' },\n  filetypes = { 'c' },\n  root_markers = { '.clangd' },\n})\nvim.lsp.enable('clangd')\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nMinimally, I expect the highlighting to not get stuck in a buggy state.  I also expect the completion to at least not insert the double open paren but I'm not sure if that is clangd's fault or neovim's.  I'd also expect setting `autotrigger = false` to disable this behavior entirely.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.1 (also v0.13.0-dev-246+gd393975b04)\n\n### Language server name/version\n\nApple clangd version 17.0.0 (clang-1700.0.13.5)\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 15.6\n\n### Log file\n\nhttps://gist.github.com/annacrombie/45537b8598825440b8c3c88e42489603",
