            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "please describe the problem concisely, don't post a video without that. e.g. in this case I can't copy-paste your sample text.\n\nhere's the repro I did:\n\ntestinit.lua:\n\n```\nvim.cmd[[source ~/.local/share/nvim/site/pack/core/opt/nvim-lspconfig/lsp/clangd.lua]]\nvim.lsp.config('clangd', {\n  -- cmd = { [[/opt/homebrew/opt/llvm/bin/clangd]] },\n})\nvim.lsp.enable('clangd')\n```\n\n```\nnvim --clean -u ~/testinit.lua test.c\n```\n\ntest.c:\n\n```c\nint foo(int a, int b)\n{\n  return 42;\n}\n\nint main(void)\n{\n  return foo\n  //        ^ c-x,c-o yields:\n  // return foo(int b, int a)\n}\n```\n\n\n\n>  how can I disable this autocompletion?\n\n    :help lsp-defaults\n\nSet 'omnifunc' to empty or to some other provider.\n\nBut autocompletion isn't enabled by default. You need to use `<c-x><c-o>`.\n\n\n## Proposal\n\n- And based on your video, you're in snippet mode but are confused about how to use snippet-mode. Perhaps we should show a message (which also mentions `:help snippet`).\n- The behavior is indeed confusing. It starts in Visual mode(?), and then if I hit tab it goes to Select mode (good). But if I go to Normal-mode, the snippet is still active...\n    - related? https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/30953",
