            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Hey, thanks for your response.  Sorry for not posting test.c, I didn't think it was necessary since it happens with any c code.  Yes it appears to be \"snippet mode\"!\n\n> Set 'omnifunc' to empty or to some other provider.\n\nTo clarify, I do like regular completions, so I wouldn't want to disable omnifunc entirely.  It is this behavior of trying to complete a function using <c-x><c-o>, and then being in a mode where pressing ( will insert a (in my case annoying) snippet.  Previously if I pressed <c-x><c-o> after an already complete function, it would just not do anything and pressing ( afterwards didn't insert a snippet. I'll try to figure out a way to disable just snippets.\n\nI think the only real bug here is then that going to normal mode doesn't clear the active snippet?",
